BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 37</H1>   
</CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>At this  
also my heart trembleth, and is moved out of his place.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD    
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>Hear attentively the noise of his   
voice, and the sound that goeth out of his mouth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD          
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>He directeth it under the whole     
heaven, and his lightning unto the ends of the earth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD      
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>After it a voice roareth: he        
thundereth with the voice of his excellency; and he will not stay them when his 
voice is heard.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>EL thundereth marvellously with his voice; great things doeth he, which we   
cannot comprehend.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>For he saith to the snow, Be thou on the earth; likewise to the small    
rain, and to the great rain of his strength.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>He sealeth up the hand of every man; that all men 
may know his work.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>Then the beasts go into dens, and remain in their places.</P></TD></TR>  
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>Out of the south cometh the 
whirlwind: and cold out of the north.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>By the breath of EL frost is given: and the     
breadth of the waters is straitened.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A         
NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>Also by watering he wearieth the thick cloud:   
he scattereth his bright cloud:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>
12</H4></TD><TD><P>And it is turned round about by his counsels: that they may  
do whatsoever he commandeth them upon the face of the world in the earth.</P>   
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>He causeth it   
to come, whether for correction, or for his land, or for mercy.</P></TD></TR>   
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Hearken unto this, O Job: 
stand still, and consider the wondrous works of EL.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD        
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>Dost thou know when ELOAHH        
disposed them, and caused the light of his cloud to shine?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>Dost thou know the balancings of  
the clouds, the wondrous works of him which is perfect in knowledge?</P></TD>   
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>How thy garments are 
warm, when he quieteth the earth by the south wind?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD        
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>Hast thou with him spread out the 
sky, which is strong, and as a molten looking glass?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD       
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>Teach us what we shall say unto   
him; for we cannot order our speech by reason of darkness.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>Shall it be told him that I       
speak? if a man speak, surely he shall be swallowed up.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD    
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>And now men see not the bright    
light which is in the clouds: but the wind passeth, and cleanseth them.</P></TD>
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4></TD><TD><P>Fair weather cometh  
out of the north: with ELOAHH is terrible majesty.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD         
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD><TD><P>Touching the SHADDAY, we cannot   
find him out: he is excellent in power, and in judgment, and in plenty of       
justice: he will not afflict.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V24><H4>  
24</H4></TD><TD><P>Men do therefore fear him: he respecteth not any that are    
wise of heart.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright 2000 by John 
